<% @page_title = 'Student Performance Analysis' %>
<div id="content">
 <h1 id="rollbook_show">Student Performance Help Page</h1>
 <p>This is the best page to understand how a student is doing in a class. There is a lot to see here. This help page breaks down a sample <em>student performance</em> page and talks about the contents of each section.</p>
 <h2>Links</h2>
 <p>The top section of a <em>student performance</em> page has links to the following pages, in order: the <em>student overview</em> page, the <em>class</em> page, and a link to the class <em>teacher</em> page. After the teacher link is an indicator of the marking period for which information is displayed on the page &ndash; here, 1, the only marking period that is not a link. If you wanted to see grade progression or category information for another marking period (if this were an actual student), you could click a marking period number. The marking period links are followed by a link to see all of Kurt (the example student)&#8217;s marks for the class. The next line has the marking period grade, percent and letter for the marking period you have chosen (90.3%, an A), and Kurt&#8217;s class rank (#1, woohoo!)</p>
 <h1><a href="#">Kurt Smith</a></h1>
 <h2 style='display:inline;margin-right:2em'><a href="#">Pre-Calculus</a>(Period 2)<a href="#">Mr Wilhour</a></h2>
 <h3 style='display:inline'>Viewing Marking Period <span style='font-size:1.3em' title='currently viewing grades for marking period 1'>1</span> <a href="#" title="If this were a real student, you could click here to see grades for marking period 2">2</a> <a href="#" title="If this were a real student, you could click to see grades for marking period 3">3</a> <a href="#" title="If this were a real student, you could click to see grades for marking period 4">4</a>  <a href="#">See all marks</a></h3>
 <h3 style='margin-top:1em'>Marking Period Grade: 90.3 (A) Class Rank 1</h3>
 <hr/>
 <h2>Academic Performance</h2>
 <p>The next section of the page shows two measures of the student&#8217;s academic performance: performance by assignment category, and performance over time.<noscript> Since you do not have Javascript enabled in your browser, you will see this information in tabular form, rather than graphical as described below.</noscript></p>
<div id='categories' style="float:left;width:60%;">
 <h3>Performance by Assignment Category</h3>
 
 <p>When an assignment is created, the teacher must give it a category. The <em>student performance</em> page shows how a student has done on assignments of each category during the marking period. In this example, Kurt has earned 380 out of 400 points on all the tests given in pre-Calculus during the first marking period. There were only 25 homework points assigned, and Kurt earned 23 of them.</p>
