</div>
 <div class="progression" style="float:left;width:38%;margin-left:10px">
 <h3 title="Marking period grade over time">Grade Progression</h3>
 
<p>This section is a history of the student&#8217;s grade over time. Kurt the example student started out strong with a 90%, then dropped down to a 63 after the second assignment. He recovered nicely though, climbing steadily back up to 92 by assignment 8 and then hovering in the high 80s/low 90s for the rest of the marking period.</p>
<img src="http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?cht=lc&amp;chd=t:90.63,72,78,73,88,92,91,87,87,5,87,87,90,89,81,90.5&amp;chs=300x130&amp;chco=66AEBD&amp;chf=c,s,eeeeee&amp;chxt=y&amp;chg=1000,20,1,0"/>
 
</div>
<hr class="clear"/>
<h2>Assignments</h2>
<p>Below the performance information are two tables on Kurt&#8217;s assignments for the class, both the recently graded ones and the ones that will be due soon. Each assignment has a link to more information about it.</p>
<div id="grades" style="float:left;width:60%;">
 <h3 title='Graded assignments due between <%= 7.days.ago.strftime("%a %b %d") %> and <%= 1.week.from_now.strftime("%a %b %d") %>'>Recently Graded Assignments</h3>
 <table class='scrollike sortable' cellspacing='0'>
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th>#</th><th>Category</th><th>Due Date</th><th>Points</th>
    <th>Score</th><th>%</th><th title='Class Average'>Class Avg (%)</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
   <tr class='<%= cycle('odd', 'even', :name => 'graded') %>'>
    <td class='text'><%= link_to '16', '#' %></td>
    <td><%= 'Classwork' %></td>
    <td><%= (Date.today - 3).strftime("%a %b %d") %></td>
    <td><%= 5 %></td>
    <td><%= 5 %></td>
    <td><%= 100.0 %></td>
    <td><%= 77.0 %></td>
   </tr>
   <% reset_cycle('graded') %>
  </tbody>
 </table>
</div>
<div id='ungraded' style="float:left;width:38%;margin-left:10px">
 <h3 title='Ungraded assignments due between <%= 7.days.ago.strftime("%a %b %d") %> and <%= 1.week.from_now.strftime("%a %b %d") %>'>Upcoming/Ungraded Assignments</h3>
 <table class='scrollike sortable' cellspacing=0>
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th>#</th><th>Category</th><th>Due Date</th><th>Points</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr class='<%= cycle('odd', 'even') %>'>
     <td><%= link_to '18', '#' %></td>
     <td><%= 'quiz' %></td>
     <td><%= (Date.today + 2).strftime("%a %b %d") %></td>
     <td><%= 25 %></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
</div>
<p class="clear" style="padding-top:1em">After the two tables of assignment information, there is a link to see the student&#8217;s grades on every assignment that has been given for the class. Unlike the grade progression and category information, the assignment information is always current. In other words, if you look back at marking period 1 data during marking period 2, you will still see the most recent assignments in the Recently Graded table.</p>
